eu_initiatives:
EFCI's main focus lies on policies in the area of:  
(i) labour market surveillance and labour law at national and European level; 
(ii) employment and social policy, including social protection; 
(iii) health and safety at the workplace; 
(iv) internal market and services; 
(v) national and European level industrial relations.  

The EFCI is currently monitoring the following issues: the implementation of the Enforcement Directive of the Posting of Workers directive adopted in 2014; the implementation of the Directive on measures facilitating the exercise of rights conferred on workers in the context of freedom of movement for workers adopted in 2014; social partners consultation on the practical implementation of the Working Time Directive and public consultation on the review of the Working Time Directive; current evaluation of Health & Safety Directives.
